An enchanting short film by directors Rocco Gurrieri and Irene Montini showcases at the recently launched SILK exhibition from the Salvatore Ferragamo Museum, drawing inspiration from the figurative world of the scarves created by Fulvia Ferragamo. A lonely girl in a place suspended between sky and sea slips tenderly into the emptiness of her days, secretly composing a variety of fantastical worlds in which she may abandon herself to her fantasies. Take a virtual tour through the link in bio. 

